history.content:
I would recommend just doing EE126, its a tough class, but they do end up reteaching a good deal of 70 in the first month and a half, so if you are a bit rusty, that will be fine. But taking both 134 and 126 is quite redundant and definitely not worth it in my opinion. 126 will teach much of the 134 material and a lot more, so I think it is a much better deal to take 126. 

*Can't comment on 140 as I am quite unfamiliar with its content, but in terms of probability practice/mastery 126 has no equal and there is little reason to take similar courses unless you really want to reinforce the concepts and are fine with the redundancy.

Would this be redundant? I don't feel ready to jump into EE 126, so I was thinking I could take a semester of Stat 134 or Stat 140 since I heard the classes are similar but also focus on different topics. I don't mind learning things twice to gain a better understanding, but would taking both be redundant? 

I have taken CS70 and did ok, but no upper division stats classes.
history.subject: Taking both Stat 134 and EE 126
